# 01_node_tool_toggle — the canonical m2 reference test.
#
# Two lines. Driven from the Curvz Scripter window (visible only in
# CURVZ_DIAGNOSTIC builds). Same shape as the sandbox m1 reference.
#
# tool.node is the Node-tool ToggleButton on the main toolbar. It's
# a normal GTK::ToggleButton augmented with the curvz::scripting
# substrate — clicking it from a script goes through the exact same
# code path as a user click, including the radio-invariant logic
# that sets it as the active tool.
#
# Run this from the Scripter window and check that:
#   1. The Node button visibly turns on in the toolbar.
#   2. The Canvas's active tool becomes Node.
#   3. The assert prints PASS.

tool.node click
assert tool.node active == true
